====================================
Nimboss: The Nimbus Provisioning API
====================================


Install
=======

Create a virtualenv:
    $ virtualenv nimboss_env

Install dependancies:
    $ pip -E nimboss_env install zope.interface httplib2 simplejson
    $ cd nimboss_env
    $ git clone git://github.com/apache/libcloud.git
    $ git clone git@github.com:clemesha-ooi/nimboss.git


Tests
=====

Nimboss currently uses Python's unittest framework.

To run tests:
    $ cd tests
    $ python tests.py




Architecture and Notes
======================


Context client
--------------
- create context
- generate userdata
- check context state (for now we adapt the ContextClient from CPE demo (later maybe swap out cloud client calls with REST calls)


ICluster interface 
------------------
- list of INodes with some extra data (?) (just need the implementation Cluster)


IClusterDriver interface
------------------------
 - create_cluster()
- destroy_cluster()
- query_cluster()
- an implementation that uses the context client

Driver implementation for each EC2 and Nimbus, that implements both INodeDriver and IClusterDriver methods.


Core module 
-----------
( what the caller imports)

Facilities: 
    - logging 
    - config 
    - errors
    - ?

